def: An unfledged bird; hence, something immature or unfinished.Ford.

An immense leguminous tree (Pithecolobium Saman) of Venezuela.Its branches form a hemispherical mass, often one hundred and eightyfeet across. The sweet pulpy pods are used commonly for feedingcattle. Also called rain tree. J. Smith (Dict. Econ. Plants).
To supply with provisions for subsistence; to provide withfood; to store with sustenance; as, to victual an army; to victual aship.I must go victual Orleans forthwith. Shak.
An extinct genus of marine reptiles allied to Plesiosaurus, buthaving a much shorter neck.
Having a tendency to form ulcers; rendering ulcerous.
Of or pertaining to a prefect.
To utter with a musical or prolonged note or tone; to chant;as, to intone the church service.
Of an expiatory nature; expiatory. Jer. Taylor.

The base or foot of a column, statue, vase, lamp, or the like;the part on which an upright work stands. It consists of three parts,the base, the die or dado, and the cornice or surbase molding. SeeIllust. of Column.Build him a pedestal, and say, "Stand there!" Cowper.
